hi, all. i'm having an issue with the `og:image` tag. i'm using the following code:
```{% if !content.featured_image %}
&lt;meta property="og:image" content="{{ get_asset_url('/KAJ_2020/images/social-generic.jpg') }}"&gt;
&lt;meta property="og:image:alt" content="{{ site_settings.company_name }}"&gt;
{% endif %}```
basically, if no featured image is selected in the Settings tab, use this fallback image. the meta tag is rendering properly in my `&lt;head&gt;` but Facebook Debugger is saying *The 'og:image' property should be explicitly provided, even if a value can be inferred from other tags.* even though it's clearly there. i've scraped again multiple times without any luck. any ideas?
